title: Egress policy defaults to deny-all when no rules are configured
---
When no access bundle or egress rules are active (e.g. DM sessions, no room profile), the Tool.egress_rules list is empty. The evaluator in egress_evaluator.ml defaults to Deny when no rules match (line ~117), so ALL outbound HTTP is blocked.

This means web_fetch, web_search, http_get, http_request all silently fail for non-room-agent sessions unless egress rules are explicitly configured.

Three issues:
1. clawq.org should be in a default allowlist (at minimum for llms-full.txt / llms.txt which the prompt builder already references).
2. There should be a configurable egress strictness setting (strict = default-deny as now; permissive = default-allow with deny rules; or a global allowlist in top-level config).
3. When egress is denied, the tool should return a more informative message suggesting the user configure egress rules or adjust strictness — not just 'egress denied: GET clawq.org /llms.txt (rule -1)'.
4. An agent can bypass egress policy trivially via bash (curl, python, wget), so the current strictness without shell enforcement is security theater unless the sandbox is enforcing network isolation.